/wiki/Mostafa_Nazari: Mostafa Nazari (Persian: مصطفی نظری‎; born 11 December 1982) is an Iranian futsal player. He is currently a member of Sunich Saveh in the Iranian Futsal Super League.
/wiki/Mostafa_Tayyebi: Mostafa Tayyebi (Persian: مصطفی طیبی‎, born 9 June 1987) is an Iranian futsal player. He is currently a member of Mes Sungun in the Iranian Futsal Super League.
/wiki/Ali_Kiaei: Seyed Ali Kiaei (Persian: سید علی کیایی‎, born 20 April 1987) is an Iranian futsal player.
/wiki/Majid_Latifi: Majid Latifi (Persian: مجید لطیفی‎, born 21 March 1981) is an Iranian retired futsal player.
/wiki/Ali_Asghar_Hassanzadeh: Ali Asghar Hassanzadeh Navlighi (Persian: علی‌اصغر حسن‌زاده ناولیقی‎, born 2 November 1987) is an Iranian futsal player. He is a Pivot, and currently a member of Giti Pasand in the Iranian Futsal Super League and the Iran national futsal team. Hassanzadeh is regarded as one of the greatest Asian futsal players in history and has been named AFC Futsal Player of the Year four times (2014, 2016, 2017, and 2018) and was a nominee for World Futsal Player of the Year in 2015. He is also the all time top goalscorer of the AFC Futsal Club Championship with 33 goals.
/wiki/Mohammad_Keshavarz: Mohammad Keshavarz Nasrabadi (Persian: محمد کشاورز نصرآبادی‎, born 5 July 1982) is an Iranian futsal player. He is a Defender, and currently a member of Giti Pasand.
/wiki/Masoud_Daneshvar: Masoud Daneshvar (Persian: مسعود دانشور‎, born 30 January 1988) is an Iranian futsal player. He is a striker, and currently a member of Sadra Shiraz.
/wiki/Mohammad_Taheri: Mohammad Taheri (Persian: محمد طاهری‎, born 5 February 1985) is an Iranian futsal player. He is a Right Winger, and currently a player of Setaregan Varamin.
/wiki/Ebrahim_Masoudi: Ebrahim Masoudi Karijani (Persian: ابراهیم مسعودی کاریجانی‎, born 16 August 1982) is an Iranian futsal player.
/wiki/Futsal_at_the_2007_Asian_Indoor_Ga: Futsal at the 2007 Asian Indoor Games was held in Macau, China from 26 October to 3 November 2007.
/wiki/Indoor_hockey_at_the_2007_Asian_In: Indoor hockey at the 2007 Asian Indoor Games was held in Macau, China from 26 October to 3 November 2007.
/wiki/Muay_Thai_at_the_2007_Asian_Indoor: Muay Thai at the 2007 Asian Indoor Games was held in Macau East Asian Games Dome, Macau, China from 29 October to 3 November 2007.
/wiki/Mohammad_Alirezaei: Mohammad Alirezaei Dizicheh (Persian: محمد علیرضایی دیزیچه‎, born 27 July 1985 in Esfahan) is an Iranian former breaststroke swimmer.
/wiki/Short_course_swimming_at_the_2007_: Short course swimming at the 2007 Asian Indoor Games was held in Macau Olympic Aquatic Centre, Macau, China from 30 October to 2 November 2007.
/wiki/Shadi_Paridar: Shadi Paridar (Persian: شادی پریدر‎; born 2 July 1986) is an Iranian chess player holding the title of Woman Grandmaster (WGM), who won Iranian Women Chess Championship four times. She won the Asian Under-16 Girls' Championship in 2002 in Tehran.
/wiki/Chess_at_the_2007_Asian_Indoor_Gam: Chess at the 2007 Asian Indoor Games was held in Macau International Shooting Range, Macau, China from 26 October to 3 November 2007.
/wiki/Esports_at_the_2007_Asian_Indoor_G: Esports at the 2007 Asian Indoor Games was held in Macau East Asian Games Dome, Macau, China from 27 October to 30 October 2007. Three events FIFA 07, NBA Live 07 and Need for Speed: Most Wanted were held in the competition.
/wiki/Ehsan_Mohajer_Shojaei: Ehsan Mohajer Shojaei (Persian: احسان مهاجر شجاعی‎, born 21 March 1983 in Borujerd) is an Iranian middle distance track athlete who specialized in the 800 metres. Mohajer Shojaei was a bronze medalist in the 2006 Asian Games and 2011 Asian Athletics Championships, a competitor at the 2008 Summer Olympics, and a gold medalist at the 2007 Summer Universiade (his first gold medal in an international competition). He was born only one day off of the birth date of fellow countryman Sajjad Moradi, with whom Shojaei ran numerous 800 metres races in international competition.
/wiki/Indoor_athletics_at_the_2007_Asian: Indoor athletics at the 2007 Asian Indoor Games was held in Macau East Asian Games Dome, Macau, China from 30 October to 1 November 2007.
/wiki/Elshan_Moradi: Elshan Moradi Abadi (Persian: الشن مرادی ابدی‎, born 22 May 1985) is a chess grandmaster from Iran. He took part in the Chess World Cup 2011, but was eliminated in the first round by Leinier Domínguez.
/wiki/Ehsan_Ghaemmaghami: Ehsan Ghaem-Maghami (Persian: احسان قائم‌مقامی‎; born August 11, 1982) is an Iranian chess grandmaster (2000). He is the record holder of Iranian Chess Championship with 13 titles.
/wiki/Homayoun_Tofighi: Tamijani Homayoon Toufighi (Persian: همایون توفیقی‎; born March 21, 1990) is an Iranian chess grandmaster (2010).
/wiki/Shayesteh_Ghaderpour: Shayesteh Ghaderpour (Persian: شایسته قادرپور‎) is an Iranian chess player who hold the title of International Women Master. She is a silver medalist the Iranian Women's Chess Championship and has represented Iran at six Chess Olympiads.
/wiki/Mitra_Hejazipour: Mitra Hejazipour (Persian: میترا حجازی‌پور‎, born 19 February 1993 in Mashhad) is an Iranian chess player who holds the title of Woman Grandmaster.
/wiki/Sajjad_Moradi: Sajjad Moradi (Persian: سجاد مرادی‎, born 30 March 1983) is an Iranian middle distance runner who specializes in the 800 metres and 1500 metres. He holds multiple national records for Iran from various track disciplines. Moradi is a gold medalist in the Asian Games, Asian Athletics Championships, Asian Indoor Games, and Universiade. He also competed at three Summer Olympic Games in 2004, 2008, and 2012.
/wiki/Mehdi_Shahrokhi: Seyed Mahdi Shahrokhi (Persian: سید مهدی شاهرخی‎, born 23 May, 1985) is an Iranian athlete specializing in the shot put. He won several medals at the regional level.
/wiki/Kabaddi_at_the_2007_Asian_Indoor_G: Kabaddi was contested by seven teams at the 2007 Asian Indoor Games in Macau, China from 30 October to 3 November. The competition took place at Luso-Chinesa School Pavilion.
